<div id="review_2757192814" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2757192814" />
    <a title="Meg Imperato" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/57438236-meg-imperato"><img alt="Meg Imperato" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1617112189p2/57438236.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2757192814?book_show_action=true">Mar 20, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Meg Imperato" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Meg Imperato" href="/user/show/57438236-meg-imperato">Meg Imperato</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/57438236-meg-imperato?shelf=classic">classic</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/57438236-meg-imperato?shelf=historical-fiction">historical-fiction</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2757192814" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10276613355804743817">I usually don&apos;t seek out books about politics, so I was surprised that this book kept my attention so well. The reader follows a flawed narrator Odili on his journey into the complicated world of post-independence politics in an unnamed African country. Elements of the book remind me of <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/4671.The_Great_Gatsby' title='The Great Gatsby by F. Scott Fitzgerald' rel='nofollow noopener'>The Great Gatsby</a>, specifically the navigation of high society through the eyes of an often cynical and judgemental character. The book is full of ironic moments that Achebe uses to highlight hypocrisy. If you are</span>
  <span id="freeText10276613355804743817" style="display:none">I usually don't seek out books about politics, so I was surprised that this book kept my attention so well. The reader follows a flawed narrator Odili on his journey into the complicated world of post-independence politics in an unnamed African country. Elements of the book remind me of <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/4671.The_Great_Gatsby" title="The Great Gatsby by F. Scott Fitzgerald" rel="nofollow noopener">The Great Gatsby</a>, specifically the navigation of high society through the eyes of an often cynical and judgemental character. The book is full of ironic moments that Achebe uses to highlight hypocrisy. If you are interested in West African history or politics, I'd definitely recommend this book.<br /><br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="10276613355804743817" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


