<div id="review_3855112983" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3855112983" />
    <a title="Unathi" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/47691097-unathi"><img alt="Unathi" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1462875014p2/47691097.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3855112983?book_show_action=true">Feb 28, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Unathi" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Unathi" href="/user/show/47691097-unathi">Unathi</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780435905347" href="/book/show/825370.A_Man_of_the_People">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3855112983" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7926276830676116798">If you&apos;re not interested in intelligent commentary on African politics don&apos;t read this. I&apos;m not too deep into political related conversations. But our lives are ruled by politicians and each of us has an opinion. This book is satirical, funny and sad, as far as how the people know the truth, but not much can be done to change the system in the great scheme of things. There is a resigned, grudging acceptance of corruption. The belief that, at least we are not as oppresses as when the whites ruled</span>
  <span id="freeText7926276830676116798" style="display:none">If you're not interested in intelligent commentary on African politics don't read this. I'm not too deep into political related conversations. But our lives are ruled by politicians and each of us has an opinion. This book is satirical, funny and sad, as far as how the people know the truth, but not much can be done to change the system in the great scheme of things. There is a resigned, grudging acceptance of corruption. The belief that, at least we are not as oppresses as when the whites ruled us. I liked it and Odi is an intelligent, idealistic man who unknowingly is as bad as the rest of the people in the story. He just gives himself a measuring stick that's shorter than the rest.<br />I enjoyed the cleverness in this book.</span>
  <a data-text-id="7926276830676116798" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


